Task 7: Configure Docker Networking
In this task, I moved beyond standalone containers to a networked architecture. 
Isolation is a core security feature of Docker, but services often need to communicate.

Implementation Steps:
Created a bridge network: 
```bash
docker network create my_network

Deployed the Database: 
Launched a MySQL container attached to the custom network.
```bash
docker run -d --name my-db --network my_network -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root mysql:latest

Deployed the Application: Connected the Node.js app to the same network.
```bash
docker run -d --name sample-app --network my_network learningwithjunoon/sample-app:v1.0

Key Insight: By using a custom network, I enabled Service Discovery. 
The application can connect to the database using the hostname my-db instead of a fluctuating IP address.
